snippet.textDisplay:
Weta Workshop are amazing. I love all of their work. They have blown my mind time and again with their expertise. I am very much looking forward to seeing what they do for Avatar 2, 3, 4 ... and 5?

FYI - I had heard a rumour James was considering using Ocolus Rifts (or another VR headset) to have limited showings of the film in VR where you could turn your head and see people or things talking or moving behind you but also be able to look around and see the entire environment in 3D. I very much wish this rumour to be true but I can imagine the experience would be extremely expensive; and may not be for the actual movies.
